In Australia and New Zealand it forms a great part of the food of the aboriginal nativos, but, like other plants that contain only starch, it is incapable of supporting life without the addition of some other substance containing nitrogenous matter. Since the colonization of these countries, and the introduction of the potato and corn, it will ere long cease to be an article of food.
